{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"1b38dc1c-9db8-4cdf-8e2c-c02a79e17625","content":"You're on **MSTest 3.8.2 / .NET 9**, so you can use **constructor injection** for `TestContext` (no more static property needed). Here's the recommended pattern:\n\n```csharp\n[TestClass]\npublic class MyTests\n{\n    private readonly TestContext _testContext;\n    private MyService _service;\n\n    // TestContext injected via constructor (MSTest v3+)\n    public MyTests(TestContext testContext)\n    {\n        _testContext = testContext;\n\n        // Synchronous init here (runs before each test)\n        _service = new MyService();\n    }\n\n    // Async init (runs after constructor, before each test)\n    [TestInitialize]\n    public async Task SetupAsync()\n    {\n        await _service.ConnectAsync();\n    }\n\n    [TestMethod]\n    public void SyncTest()\n    {\n        Assert.IsNotNull(_service);\n        _testContext.WriteLine(\"Test passed!\");\n    }\n\n    [TestMethod]\n    public async Task AsyncTest()\n    {\n        var result = await _service.GetDataAsync();\n        Assert.IsNotNull(result);\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n\n- **Constructor** — sync init + `TestContext` injection (MSTest 3+ feature; replaces the old `public TestContext TestContext { get; set; }` property pattern)\n- **`[TestInitialize]`** — supports `async Task` for async setup\n- **Execution order:** Constructor → `[TestInitialize]` → Test → `[TestCleanup]`","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"d9f280c6-b6cc-4fb2-b4c2-a5f5503d2074","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"They're using MSTest 3.8.2 on .NET 9.0. In MSTest v3, the recommended approach has evolved. Let me provide the modern patterns.\n\nIn MSTest 3.x:\n- `TestContext` can be injected via constructor (this is the modern way, available since MSTest 3.x)\n- `[TestInitialize]` for synchronous init\n- `[TestInitialize]` also supports async (returns `Task`) since MSTest v3\n- `[ClassInitialize]` for class-level init\n- Constructor injection of `TestContext` is the recommended approach in MSTest 3.x\n\n\nNow I'll put together a clear, practical answer with examples.","outputTokens":548,"requestId":"7C12:1E67:17EE4F:1CC49F:69F94883"},"id":"f6bf3e69-f32f-4249-aa02-ceceb23c6559","timestamp":"2026-05-05T01:31:58.869Z","parentId":"f739e5ef-c0ef-4c79-a92a-0e2ec6f7c09e"}
